ODM party officials have warned Dagoretti North MP Simba Arati over his move to open parallel party offices.  Addressing a delegates meeting yesterday, the leaders who included Governor James Ongwae, Senator Sam Ongeri and Woman Rep Janet Ongera said they will not join those intent to split the party.  Ongwae said voters will decide on who will win the party ticket for the county top seat.   Last week, Arati and Kitutu Chache MP Richard Onyonka opened party offices across the nine constituencies in Kisii.    Siaya Senator Orengo denies ODM has drawn line-up  Consult party leadership first, Oparanya warns Wanjigi  Anybody ready to help Baba cane Wa-Jigy?   Raila banks on consensus to avert fallout of allies in elections  Pulpit Politics: ODM leader Raila Odinga welcomes move to ban politicians speaking in church  Raila comes up with a platform which he says will harmonize major issues affecting ordinary citizens  Wawaniaji wa nafasi ya Ugavana kaunti ya Mombasa kupitia chama cha ODM wajiandaa By Nathan Ochunge | 2 hours ago By Allan Mungai | 11 hours ago By Chris Thairu | 19 hours ago By Judah Ben-Hur | 19 hours ago